cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.CY 

This paper deals with natural language processing and machine learning techniques to improve text prediction and completion. Specifically, it focuses on clinical text prediction, which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also discusses the use of neural language models, which is a popular topic in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the incorporation of a structured knowledge base and numerical values into the context used for prediction suggests a potential application in information retrieval (cs.IR) and cybernetics (cs.CY).
